node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lorp Gribs 🍩 on July 30, 2021. May be an anime-style image of 1 person and text that says '৩'.

node.text:
Some of you might remember this one from way back in 2018! I made it as part of a giveaway so somebody out there has the original of this and I hope they’re enjoying it ❤️For some reason when I made this I didn’t think it was going to be very well liked, so when I shipped it off I didn’t even bother to take a professional picture to make it into a print or anything like that. Years later I found out that not only did a bunch of people love it but my bf informed me that it’s always been his favorite piece often and that he was super sad I gave it away. Ever since then I wanted to remake it for him so it’s been sitting on my agenda for a while now and I’m really happy I got a moment to do it. I struggled with this one a bit but I think it turned out really pretty. You can swipe to see the original to compare and contrast ❤️

#sketch #drawing #art #copic #anime #manga #procreate #kawaii #pretty #instagramart #dibujo #portland #oregon #clouds

node.text:
July’s patreon rewards have arrived at my home and they look awesome! I can’t wait to mail them to you guys. The sticker tier gets this holographic headspace sticker and the print tier comes with the sticker + my first ever custom area holographic print (usually the print has Holo all over but it’s just in a few spots here which looks nice!) if you want these rewards there’s still a few days left to sign up, as long as you join by the end of the month you’re good to go! Patreon ships out worldwide with free shipping,  link is in my bio!

#sticker #slap #slaptag #kawaii #anime #art #sticker #portland #oregon

node.text: If you guys watch my stories you probably hear about @matt_linares fairly often, although I realized if you look at my page you probably have no idea who he is. Matt is someone who has played a big influence on my growth as a painter. I met him years ago now, before I worked as an artist for a job. I was trying to hire him for project I working on, I saw some of his art in a FB group and was immediately blown away, it reminded me of Star Wars meets Salvador Dali and I just had to talk to him. My project ended up going nowhere but I still loved his art and wanted to learn to paint like him so I asked him one day if he’d teach me to paint clouds, and he very graciously let me come to his studio and gave me some pointers. I learned a lot from him about brushes and technique and wrist movement, all the kinds of things I had hoped art school would teach me but never did. I absolutely fell in love with his studio space, a hundred year old building that used to be a seed factory and it wasn’t long before we were full fledged art studio mates and I had several of Matt’s paintings hanging in my house. It’s been about 6 years now since we met and I still look up to Matt tremendously, he’s extremely talented and hard working and all around just one of my favorite people.  A long time ago we made a little drawing on a shipping label and it served as the inspiration for this full fledged piece, you can swipe to see it. It means so much that to me that we got to make this painting together since I got to make art on the same canvas as someone I admire so much. I hope you guys take a moment to go look at the stunning art of @matt_linares, anything I know about acrylic paint I learned from him exclusively. I always tell him to make tutorials so that you guys can learn too! Honestly if that’s something you guys would want leave him a comment or send him a pestering message maybe he’ll finally do it, his tips really are so helpful. But I’m just really happy we made this piece together.  #painting #acrylic #paint #traditional #glow #kawaii #dendrobot #collab #portland #oregon #artist #instagramart

Headspace: This is one of my favorite pin designs so I thought it was high time I make a full illustration out of it.
Good news! I was safely able to get up to Seattle over the weekend and drop off all my product. Driving with all my product in one van was really intimidating, it was such a relief to get it dropped off. I have some more tweaks I’m doing to the store and some restocks that’s need to get done but i’m hoping sometime in August the store can open! Please let me know if there’s something you’d like to see in there like a specific print or keychain or something!

node.text:
Sort of an oldie if you’ve been around long enough to remember it but one of my favs:The Polaroid gals! The face on the one on the right always bothered me so I changed it a bit and I’m reposting. How is your guys’ weekends going? I’m up in Seattle right now because I just made a huge move of dropping all my product off at a fulfillment center. That means in the future I can have my shop open more often because they’ll handle all the storage and shipping, I’m really excited and honestly it’s such a weight off my shoulders. I was scared the whole way driving up that I was going to crash and lose all my product or something, it was a huge sigh of relief to deliver all the boxes and now I’m going to explore Seattle a bit before heading home! 
#polaroid #camera #art #kawaii #artist #isometric #interesting #rainbow #goop

node.text:
‘Idk why but ever since I got my vaccine I can’t stop thinking about how much I love Microsoft products and hanging up pictures of Bill Gates, my 5G has never been better though’

I wanted to make a cute vaccine Chan to celebrate being fully vaccinated:

It’s been about a month since I got my vaccine and it’s been so amazing for my mental health . I’ve been able to do go to the gym, see/hug friends and family, go to restaurants, and just in general be out in the world having fun, and living my life. I still wear my mask when I’m out but I don’t feel cooped up inside isolated living the same day over and over anymore. I wasn’t sure how much longer I could take living like that and I’m sure I’m not alone in that feeling. I’ve felt so sad especially for all the younger people who missed out on core life experiences this last year, particularly not being able to attend school and see peers or teachers or attend graduation, those were really precious times for me and you can’t get those back so I imagine that must have been really hard for you guys. I know things aren’t over yet, but this bit of freedom has given me so much hope that there’s a light at the end of this crazy tunnel that started so abruptly over a year ago. It’s just really nice to feel like a human again and not feel scared every time I set foot outside my house. Hope you guys are doing well also! ❤️

#kawaii #anime #art #artwork #procreate #digital #traditital

node.text:
EDIT! The deadline is extended to 7/20 It’s been ages since my last draw this in your style challenge I’ve really missed hosting them. I’m super excited to be finally hosting a new one, for a long time I couldn’t think of a good character for it but I came up with this little character named Mana for it and I think she’s so adorable. I always love seeing the amazing talent and vast array of styles you guys have whenever I do these, I end up discovering lots of cool new artists and it makes my heart so warm seeing how wonderfully kind and supportive you are to each other. ;w;
So here’s the rules:

1.) Recreate this character in your style. Any medium is welcome here, drawing, sculpting, make-up, photography, photoshop etc. It doesn’t have to be in this pose, create her however you like as long as it looks like the character (gender bending is totally good too) 

2.) Post it to your page and make sure you add the hashtag #manaredraw, please remember that if you have an account set to private even if you use the hashtag I will not be able to see your entry. (If you’re having issues with your entry showing up in the hashtag make sure to tag me in the photo directly)

3: that’s it! The deadline is July 11th so you have lots of time to get around to it. Have fun creating, be loving and support one another, and make some new friends! I can’t wait to celebrate all your unique styles and see what you guys make! 

#dtiys #drawthisinyourstyle #characterdrsign #drawing #procreate #redraw #mana #anime #otaku #kawaii

node.text:
The pencil really shouldn’t be there any more because the original drawing deviated so far from the sketch but I left it in out of sheer S P I T E . Sometimes you have an idea and you draw it like 59 times and it does not go well / turn out how you were imagining which can be really frustrating. That’s the kind of stuff that makes you turn on yourself with ugly self shame ‘I’m a fraud! I’m not a real artist like all those other artists that get an idea and then whip it out perfectly on their first try’. But the truth is, anybody who always get the art right on the first try is either a psychopath that made a pact with the devil for that power, or a really old master who has been at it 124757357 hours (but mostly psychopaths). If you want a big mood just google ‘Miyazaki with art block’ and you’ll instantly feel less alone in the world. It works I swear, give it a go, and be nicer to yourself if your final piece ends up different than you planned because I bet it’s a bangin piece (you can still be full of spite though that’s totally fine) 

#drawing #summer #art #popsicle #anime #manga #otaku #ribbon #hair #floral #flowers #kawaii
